        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Our Irvine restaurant is in a new development. Do we need a suppression system if the building is brand new?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Yes. Building age is irrelevant to NFPA 96 compliance. Any commercial cooking operation producing grease-laden vapors requires an automatic wet chemical suppression system regardless of building age. California-licensed fire protection contractors must design, install, and inspect the system. Semi-annual inspection begins immediately at opening.</p></div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 mt-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 mb-8"><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Does every Irvine restaurant need a kitchen fire suppression system?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Yes. All commercial cooking operations in Irvine producing grease-laden vapors must have an automatic wet chemical suppression system under NFPA 96 and the California Fire Code (Title 19 CCR). This applies to restaurants, bars with food service, hotel kitchens, and corporate cafeterias.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How often does kitchen fire suppression need to be inspected in Irvine?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">NFPA 96 requires semi-annual inspection — twice per year — for all commercial kitchen suppression systems. Inspection must be performed by a licensed contractor and documented. The Irvine Fire Department enforces this requirement.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How much does kitchen suppression inspection cost in Irvine?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">$175–$380 per system per system. Budget for two inspections annually.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">What is the most common kitchen fire safety violation in Irvine?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Common violations in Irvine include: Overdue semi-annual suppression in Irvine Spectrum restaurant tenants — high turnover creates compliance gaps; Corporate cafeteria suppression not on semi-annual schedule.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Who licenses kitchen suppression contractors in CA?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">The California State Fire Marshal's Office ((916) 445-8200) licenses fire protection contractors statewide. Verify your suppression contractor holds current CA credentials before scheduling service.</p></div></div>
